text = "[b][font_size=21]How to use the SceneMap Plugin[/font_size][/b]
[b]Adding components to a scene[/b]
[ol]
 Create a new script that inherits from the  [bgcolor=#1a1a1a][code]SceneMapComponent2D[/code][/bgcolor]  class. For more information check the class documentation or the GitHub page.
 Add a node in the scene and attach that script to it.
[/ol]

[b]Adding scenes to the map[/b]
[ol]
 Use the [img=%20]res://addons/scene_map_plugin/assets/add-icon.svg[/img] or button drag a .tscn file to add a new scene to the map.
 Drag and drop the arrow slots [img=%18]res://addons/scene_map_plugin/assets/arrow-double.svg[/img] to connect one scene to another.
 Use the controls in each slot to disconnect them [img=%18]res://addons/scene_map_plugin/assets/disconnect-icon.svg[/img] or change their side [img=%18]res://addons/scene_map_plugin/assets/sides-icon.svg[/img], type [img=%18]res://addons/scene_map_plugin/assets/type-icon.svg[/img] or name [img=%18]res://addons/scene_map_plugin/assets/edit-icon.svg[/img]
 Use the [img=%20]res://addons/scene_map_plugin/assets/refresh-icon.svg[/img] button to refresh all nodes in the map.
 Press DEL while having one or more nodes selected to remove them from the map.
[/ol]

[b]Configuring the components[/b]
[indent]The script that you create to inherit from the  [bgcolor=#1a1a1a][code]SceneMapComponent2D[/code][/bgcolor]  class must override the  [bgcolor=#1a1a1a][code]go_to_next_scene()[/code][/bgcolor]  method. You can check the documentation of that method in the script editor or in the GitHub page.[/indent]

[b]Adding sub-components[/b]
[indent]You can add sub-components to provide additional functionalities to the SceneMap components. To do so, simply add one of this nodes as a child to your component:
[ul]
 [bgcolor=#1a1a1a][code]SceneMapComponentArea2D[/code][/bgcolor] : triggers the component when the player enters the area.
 [bgcolor=#1a1a1a][code]SceneMapComponentMarker2D[/code][/bgcolor] : places a marker visible only in the editor that overrides the component's position. Teleporting to this component will spawn the player in the marker's position instead of the component's center position.
[/ul][/indent]

[b]Notes and recommendations[/b]
[ul]
 It is recommended to close all scenes while working with this plugin.
 You can double click on a node to open the scene in the editor.
 The âš  symbol next to a node's name means that the node has disconnected slots.
[/ul]"

